INSERT INTO `event` VALUES (19,'To be filled in ','Yoga on Wednesdays',14,0,2,NULL,1,'To be filled in....'),(20,'Free - All welcome. Please note that weekly meditations on Wednesday or Friday, 7pm &ndash; 8pm will not take place if there is a teaching in the programme. Please check the main programme.','Shinay Meditation',13,0,NULL,NULL,1,'To be filled in........'),(22,'To be filled in.....','Martial Arts',21,0,NULL,NULL,1,'To be filled in.........'),(23,'To be filled in...........','Introduction to Meditation',9,0,NULL,15,1,'To be filled in..........'),(24,'To be filled in............','Yoga on Thursdays',15,0,NULL,25,1,'To be filled in.........'),(25,'To be filled in.......','Guru Rinpoche Tsok Puja',13,0,2,12,1,'To be filled in.'),(26,'ma Yeshe Losal Rinpoche, Abbot of Samye Ling Monastery and Director of the Holy Isle Project will be at Kagyu Samye Dzong London for two days of teaching. A Master who has spent many years in solitary retreat, Lama Yeshe Rinpoche&rsquo;s teachings are always fresh, relevant and inspiring. As these teachings are always hugely popular we strongly advise that you book in advance.','Living Dharma Teachings ',10,0,2,21,1,'To be filled in.'),(27,'This course for complete beginners will focus on learning the Tibetan Alphabet and how to spell, read and write. Elements of Tibetan grammar and vocabulary will also be introduced. Bring pen and paper. It is essential to book in advance. The course will only run if there are enough participants.','Tibetan Language for Beginners',9,0,2,15,1,''),(33,'Lama Yeshe will ....','Living Dharma: Teachings and Refuge',10,0,NULL,21,1,'the text goes here'),(38,'Stress may seem to arise due to external factors, but circumstances will always be sometimes favourable, sometimes unfavourable. We need to see that it is our mind that creates our world and to learn to be comfortable with whatever arises. Compassion is at the heart of this process. This course will include a number of stress reduction exercises.\r\n','Stress Reduction Based on Compassion',37,0,10,NULL,1,''),(39,'The day will be devoted to practice as a way of overcoming obstacles and freeing beings from suffering. The practice will be dedicated to the long life and activity of HH Karmapa and our lineage masters.','Green_Tara_Day',9,0,10,NULL,1,''),(40,'The day will be devoted to practice as a way of overcoming obstacles and freeing beings from suffering. The practice will be dedicated to the long life and activity of HH Karmapa and our lineage masters.','Green Tara Day - May 2010',9,0,10,NULL,1,''),(42,'Prepare for the opening of Kagyu Samye Dzong Spa Road','Volunteer_Weekend',13,0,NULL,NULL,2,'With the auspicious occasion of the opening of our magnificent permanent new home this month, your help is needed to make sure that everything is ready for this exciting and joyful event. Join us for a very special volunteer weekend. Share in a real piece of history and help ensure that this wonderful event is a success. Lunch provided on both days. '),(43,'Tibetan meditation practice with both sitting and slow movement forms. Weekend lead by Ann Overzee','Kum_Nye',9,0,NULL,NULL,1,'This practice weekend offers an opportunity to experience the Kum Nye Tibetan meditation practice, which involves both sitting and slow movement forms. Kum Nye works on the physical, emotional and energetic blockages held in our bodies, allowing us to re-connect with our aliveness and natural flow of energy. Wear loose comfortable clothes. Bring vegetarian lunch to share.\r\n\r\nAnne Overzee is a long-term meditation practitioner. She is also an experienced psychotherapist working with mindfulness-based meditation techniques within the framework of traditional psychotherapy.'),(45,'Volunteer day at both Centres!','Volunteer_Day',13,0,8,8,1,'Come along and help us with a variety of jobs around the Kagyu Samye Dzong centres. Lunch and refreshments will be provided. Please let us know in advance if you can come.'),(46,'A day of practice to help us overcome inner and outer obstacles. The day will be dedicated ','Green_Tara_Day_July',9,0,8,4,1,'This day will be devoted to practice as a way of overcoming obstacles and freeing beings from suffering. The practice will be dedicated to the long life and activity of HH Karmapa and our lineage masters.'),(47,'Teachings with Khenpo Lhabu or Drupon Rinpoche.','Drupon_Rinpoche',48,0,8,36,1,'Drupon Rinpoche, also known as Khenpo Lhabu, has spent much time in retreat and has received teachings from HH 17th Karmapa, the 12th Tai Situ Rinpoche and Thrangu Rinpoche. The latter asked Drupon Rinpoche to become retreat master for the traditional retreat at the site of Milarepa‚Äôs cave in Nepal in 2004. Drupon Rinpoche will be teaching during this period on the Heart Sutra, the Prajnaparamita and other topics. More details of the course will be on our website and in our newsletter closer to the time. Please keep a look out or contact the office for bookings. '),(49,'Summer volunteer day','August_Volunteer_Day',13,0,8,26,1,'Help us to keep the centre clean and tidy and welcoming and have a fun day too. Lunch included. Please let us know in advance if you can come.'),(50,'let go of ego-clinging and self-importance and work for the welfare of others.','Seven_Points_of_Mind_Training',9,0,NULL,18,1,''),(51,'The wonder and colour of everyday experience can be opened up to us through increased awareness and understanding.','Meditation_&_Visualisation',37,0,NULL,32,1,'The wonder and colour of everyday experience can be opened up to us through increased awareness and understanding. If we can combine this with mindfulness we can come to see ordinary things in an extraordinary way. This course will aid this process by focussing on exercises of breathing meditation and visualisation, helping us to relax and improve. '),(52,'how to live a happy and useful life','Restoring_The_Balance',37,0,8,27,1,'Choje Akong Tulku Rinpoche‚Äôs book \"Restoring the Balance\" offers deep insight into how to live a happy and useful life. This course will focus on some vivid topics from the book such as freedom, our true nature, developing compassion. Clive is the editor of this book and will use this weekend to lead some of the exercises from it.');
